<pre><code>&lt;?php if($_COOKIE['lang'] != 'en') echo '&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="css/'.$_COOKIE['lang'].'.css"/&gt;'; ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>With this above script you get the stylesheet for the language that is selected. Like if you select France you get the stylesheet <code>fr.css</code></p>  <p>But now I want the same for <code>IE</code> so I thought something like this.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php if($_COOKIE['lang'] != 'en') echo '&lt;link rel="stylesheet" href="css/'.$_COOKIE['lang'].'ie.css"/&gt;'; ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>So now when you click on <code>France</code> it also opens <code>frie.css</code> But what do I write in here to make it only for <code>IE</code></p>  <pre><code>&lt;!--[if IE]&gt;&lt;style&gt;@import url('/css/ie.css');&lt;/style&gt;&lt;![endif]--&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Thanks!</p>